#### **PA Chest - Chest Wall**

This is a normal PA chest xray. When the image is taken, the scapula is protracted to minimize its overlap with the chest wall. Can you see where the medial border of the scapula is overlapping with the chest wall? Notice that the anterior and posterior parts of the ribs are superimposed. The portion of the rib that is more horizontal is the posterior part, while the anterior part of the rib slopes from superior to inferior.

