**BONUS:**
Counting ribs on a CXR is a skill that requires some practice. Radiologists typically find rib 1 and count from there. On the right side of the patient, see if you can find the intersection between the anterior part of the 5th rib and the posterior part of the 8th rib. When you add the labels to the image a dot will appear at this intersection.

