**Cardiomegaly**

This is a comparison of a normal-sized heart (right image) with an enlarged heart (left image). Notice that the enlarged heart is more globular in shape. The left heart borders is closer to the left lateral chest wall, and the right heart border extends out farther from the spine compared to the normal heart.

